OL,3,C'From the sublime to the ridiculous':
OL,4,CFarmer's crop concerns amid June
OL,5,Cheatwave
OL,7,FShe told ITV News Central: "Through
OL,8,Fthe winter when the grass stops
OL,9,Fgrowing, and isn't as tasty for the
OL,10,Fsheep, it's (the hay) what the sheep
OL,11,Feat.
OL,13,F"It's what keeps them growing, what
OL,14,Fkeeps their babies growing and
OL,15,Fprogressing. without it its really
OL,16,Fdifficult really."
OL,18,FShe added, "The weather has been more
OL,19,Fextreme the last few years. We've had
OL,20,Fvery wet summers and we've had
OL,21,Fincredibly hot summers.
